The curtains came down on what has been an exciting and engaging month-long affair as the glamorous The Asian Weekly Achievers Awards (Tawaa) 2017 award-ceremony took place at the Loresho SightFirst Eye Hospital on March 4.Fashion was at the brim as many came in style. It was a massive event with an august gathering of approximately 600 people attending the glamorous eveningAmong the notable guests present at the ceremony were Indian High Commissioner Suchitra Durai, University of Nairobi Chancellor Dr Vijoo Rattansi, human rights lawyer and poet Pheroze Nowrojee and Asian Foundation chairman Dr Chandu Sheth, among other dignitaries.